# Transform Traffic Engine ‚Üí Ambulance Dispatch System

Convert the existing traffic simulation into a full ambulance dispatch system with real-map rendering, dispatch algorithms, and interactive emergency features.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend: Dispatch Module

#### [NEW] [models.py](file:///c:/Users/adhiy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/traffic%20engine/backend/app/dispatch/models.py)

Data models for the dispatch system:
- `Ambulance` ‚Äî id, name, location (node ID), status (available/dispatched/returning)  
- `Hospital` ‚Äî id, name, location, capacity, current_load
- `Emergency` ‚Äî id, location, severity (1‚Äì5), timestamp
- `DispatchResult` ‚Äî assigned ambulance, hospital, algorithm used, response time, path

#### [NEW] [greedy.py](file:///c:/Users/adhiy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/traffic%20engine/backend/app/dispatch/greedy.py)

**Greedy (Naive) dispatch**: assigns the nearest available ambulance by Dijkstra distance. Sends patient to nearest hospital. Simple O(A √ó Dijkstra) where A = ambulance count.

#### [NEW] [hungarian.py](file:///c:/Users/adhiy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/traffic%20engine/backend/app/dispatch/hungarian.py)

**Hungarian Algorithm**: optimal assignment when multiple emergencies are pending. Builds a cost matrix (ambulances √ó emergencies) using Dijkstra distances, solves the assignment problem in O(n¬≥). Also factors in hospital capacity + traffic congestion for multi-objective scoring.

#### [NEW] [dispatch_service.py](file:///c:/Users/adhiy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/traffic%20engine/backend/app/dispatch/dispatch_service.py)

Central orchestrator:
- Manages ambulance fleet + hospital registry
- Maintains emergency queue
- `dispatch_greedy()` ‚Äî single emergency assignment
- `dispatch_hungarian()` ‚Äî batch optimal assignment
- `generate_emergency()` ‚Äî random emergency at a graph node
- `compare_methods()` ‚Äî runs both and returns side-by-side results
- Auto-generates emergencies during simulation ticks

#### [MODIFY] [routes.py](file:///c:/Users/adhiy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/traffic%20engine/backend/app/api/routes.py)

New endpoints:
- `GET /dispatch/state` ‚Äî ambulances, hospitals, pending emergencies
- `POST /dispatch/emergency` ‚Äî trigger a random emergency
- `POST /dispatch/assign` ‚Äî assign using specified algorithm
- `POST /dispatch/compare` ‚Äî compare greedy vs hungarian
- `POST /dispatch/reset` ‚Äî reset ambulance positions
- WebSocket: push `emergency_new`, `dispatch_assigned` events

